description: Blood-based biological age assessment using the PhenoAge formula analyzes 9 key biomarkers—albumin, creatinine, glucose, CRP, lymphocytes, mean cell volume, red cell distribution width, alkaline phosphatase, and white blood cell count—to reveal how fast your body is truly aging.
